
any folder can become a container for files

create the meta-dir (...) and add an id

the container can now be used to run tasks
data will be synced with storage services
and to other instances of the same container

as a container tasks can be created to make changes to the container

for instance; a folder full of videos can be coded to auto-convert the
video files to mp4.  the files will then be copied to a task and
the task will do the conversion and copy the new file back

a folder can be tagged local-temp so that the local copy will be removed when
it is completely copied to some storage service.

tagging a folder 'download' would cause jobs to wait for files to be constant
for some time before copying them out.  plus they would stay local for a period
of time before they are removed.
